{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"crow-knelt-fiber","description":"# WS3 — Escalation scripted ops + the code-review workflow\n\n## Why\nThis is the heart of the gate: wire WS1's base + WS2's overlays into the two-round overlay-escalation topology and feed all findings into the shipped kernel Pass-2/3/4. The mechanism was DERISKED on the real v3 engine (offline) — the agent's `recommend_overlays` drove a second batch's membership, bogus ids dropped, the cap bounded fan-out, one-hop held — so this is implementation of a proven design, with NO core-engine change.\n\n## What\n- Two deterministic scripted ops: `overlay_union` (compute (glob U base.recommend) - already-run, ONE-HOP, capped at N=3 configurable; emit per-overlay `include_<overlay>` flags + `to_run`) and `merge_findings` (concatenate base + Round-A + Round-B finding lists).\n- The thin `gates/code-review.yaml`: assemble_diff -> triggers (overlay_triggers) -> base (agent) -> round_a (batch, when:=triggers) -> union -> round_b (batch, when:=union) -> merge -> verify (Pass-2) -> decide (Pass-3) -> coach_gate/coach (Pass-4).\n\n## Scope\n- `src/rebar/llm/code_review/workflow_ops.py` (or register in `workflow/steps.py`) — `overlay_union`, `merge_findings`.\n- `src/rebar/llm/workflow/gates/code-review.yaml` — the gate workflow.\n- OUT OF SCOPE: the `gate_dispatch` entry + source-separation (WS4); the secrets/security auto-block detectors (WS5).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `overlay_union` computes (glob U recommend) - already-run, ONE-HOP, capped at N=3 (configurable), enum-constrained; `merge_findings` concatenates the three finding sources.\n- [ ] `gates/code-review.yaml` validates (`rebar workflow validate`) and runs on the v3 engine; Round-A overlays are glob-triggered, Round-B membership = the escalated union, all findings flow into kernel Pass-2/3/4.\n- [ ] An OFFLINE (FakeRunner) test asserts: Round-B membership == the escalated set; the cap bounds fan-out; one-hop holds (overlays do not re-escalate); escalation can never change the deterministic verdict.\n- [ ] The gate calls the kernel `verify_findings` / `pass3_over_findings` / `coach` directly (no forked passes).\n","id":"8855-e5f9-05b4-4a04","parent_id":"b744-4fb9-2d05-4b49","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"WS3: overlay_union + merge_findings scripted ops + gates/code-review.yaml (two-round -> kernel Pass-2/3/4)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782620577276535001,"uuid":"fe8a7430-bae7-45b1-9724-4f2194072720"}